ø1   Demo Compos....

   This  year  there will be two  catagories for the Demos. Accelerated and
    non-Accelerated.  Prizes will be biassed towards non-Accelerated demos,
    so  if  you want to win  something decent, make a non-accelerated demo.
    There will be no distinction between DOS and Win32 demos this year, the
    general  opinion being that they are as fast as each other. In fact I'd
    encourage  you  to work on win32 demos  as  they will generally be much
    easier  to get working and demos that don't run under the compo machine
    may  be  disqualified.  This along  with  the  overwhelming majority of
    win95/98/NT machines around these days.

    Rules for Non-accelerated demos.
      - Demo  archive must remain under 5mb, unarchived demo mustn't exceed
         10mb.
      - Demo must support SoundBlaster16 (can optionally support gus)
      - Demo may not write any information to disk.
      - These  demos  may  not  use any  3d  acceleration  features  of the
         hardware  present by default, but may, with a command-line option,
ø4==ø1Compo Details (continued)

         use them.
      - If  these demos have an acceleration  feature, they may not partake
         in  the  accelerated  division of the  competitions,  even if in a
         modified form. The organisers' decision is final on whether or not
         a demo entered into the accelerated division is too similar to one
         entered in this division.

    Rules for Accelerated demos.
      - Demo  archive must remain under 5mb, unarchived demo mustn't exceed
         10mb.
      - Demo must support SoundBlaster16 (can optionally support gus)
      - Demo may not write any information to disk.
      - The demo may use either Direct3D or Glide for 3d acceleration.
      - If  these  demos  have an  non-acceleration  feature,  they may not
         partake  in the non-accelerated division of the competitions, even
         if  in  a  modified  form. The  organisers'  decision  is final on
         whether or not a demo entered into the non-accelerated division is
         too similar to one entered in this division.
