A ø4crossfadeø5 is when one pic fades into another, as you can often see in films.

The first thing we need are two piccies and their palettes. They should best be
put  into different graphics pages in the VGA memory, or virtual screens if the
mode used does not support more that one page. We also require a third page, as
well  as  a third and fourth palette  for calculations. For every pixel, we now
look  at  the colour of that point in  either of the two piccies. We generate a
knew  colour index. In the 3rd palette  (the "fade from" palette) the colour is
set  to that in the first image, while it is set to that of the second image in
the  4th palette (the "fade to" palette).  Finally, a pixel with the new colour
index  is  set  on  the  3rd virtual  page.  For  every  colour combination, we
certainly  make  sure  that there isn't  already  a  colour index whose from/to
values correspond to the combination under consideration.

